WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.100
A Tale of Two Cities by Charles Dickens Retold by

00:06.100 --> 00:16.760
Stephen Coborne

00:21.140 --> 00:23.720
Chapter 1 to Dover

00:25.480 --> 00:30.240
It was the year 1775. A coach was going from

00:30.240 --> 00:33.820
London to Dover. The road was wet and muddy.

00:34.820 --> 00:37.200
The horses pulled the heavy coach slowly.

00:38.480 --> 00:41.640
A man on a horse came along the road behind

00:41.640 --> 00:44.060
the coach. He was riding quickly.

00:46.240 --> 00:47.880
Stop! Shouted the rider.

00:48.820 --> 00:52.240
What do you want? Ask the coach driver.

00:53.180 --> 00:58.280
I have a message. Shouted the rider. He stopped his

00:58.280 --> 00:59.560
horse in front of the coach.

01:00.360 --> 01:01.780
The coach also stopped.

01:03.100 --> 01:05.820
The message is for Mr Jarvis Laurie.

01:06.820 --> 01:07.660
Said the rider.

01:07.660 --> 01:11.520
A man looked out of the window of the coach.

01:12.420 --> 01:16.080
He was about sixty years old and he wore old

01:16.080 --> 01:16.980
-fashioned clothes.

01:18.160 --> 01:20.120
He saw the rider and asked,

01:20.620 --> 01:22.820
What news do you bring, Jerry?

01:24.040 --> 01:28.100
Do you know this man, sir? asked the coach driver.

01:28.880 --> 01:30.540
There are robbers on this road.

01:31.540 --> 01:34.940
I know him, replied the old man.

01:35.660 --> 01:40.000
His name is Jerry Cruncher. He has come from my

01:40.000 --> 01:40.340
bank.

01:41.120 --> 01:44.740
Jerry Cruncher is a messenger, not a robber.

01:46.060 --> 01:49.880
Here is a letter for you, Mr Laurie, the messenger

01:49.880 --> 01:50.300
said.

01:50.960 --> 01:54.360
Mr Telson wants you to wait at the Royal George

01:54.360 --> 01:55.640
Inn at Dover.

01:55.640 --> 01:59.320
A young lady will travel to Paris with you.

02:00.900 --> 02:05.780
Thank you, Jerry. Mr Laurie said. He took the letter.

02:06.520 --> 02:09.900
I will wait in Dover. Good night.

02:18.040 --> 02:21.700
At the top of the letter were the words Telson's

02:21.700 --> 02:24.040
Bank, Temple Bar, London.

02:24.040 --> 02:28.360
The date on the letter was the 18th of November

02:28.360 --> 02:30.100
1775.

02:31.660 --> 02:34.400
To Mr Jarvis Laurie, the letter said.

02:35.260 --> 02:39.760
We have news from Telson's Bank in Paris. Dr Manet

02:39.760 --> 02:40.760
is alive.

02:42.080 --> 02:44.880
He is living at the wine shop of Mischa and

02:44.880 --> 02:48.060
Madame Defarge in San Antoine, Paris.

02:48.800 --> 02:52.940
Dr Manet is ill. He was in prison for 18

02:52.940 --> 02:53.540
years.

02:54.940 --> 02:59.360
Lucy Manet, Dr Manet's daughter, will meet you in Dover.

03:00.600 --> 03:04.540
Go to the Royal George Inn in Dover. Wait for

03:04.540 --> 03:05.780
Lucy Manet there.

03:06.880 --> 03:11.220
Lucy has never met her father. Take Lucy to Paris

03:11.220 --> 03:11.920
with you.

03:12.720 --> 03:16.240
Then bring Dr Manet and Lucy back to London.

03:18.060 --> 03:21.560
The name at the bottom of the letter was Telson.

03:24.660 --> 03:27.960
Mr Laurie waited at the Royal George Inn at Dover.

03:29.000 --> 03:32.760
Miss Lucy Manet arrived the next day. She was about

03:32.760 --> 03:36.500
18 years old and she had long golden hair.

03:37.800 --> 03:43.440
Miss Manet said Mr Laurie. I work for Telson's Bank.

03:43.440 --> 03:48.420
There is a Telson's Bank in London and a Telson's

03:48.420 --> 03:49.500
Bank in Paris.

03:50.280 --> 03:55.500
I often travel between the two cities. 20 years ago

03:55.500 --> 03:59.560
your father came to Telson's Bank in Paris.

04:00.360 --> 04:04.600
Said Mr Laurie. He left some money in the bank.

04:05.600 --> 04:11.260
Yes, said Lucy Manet. My father went to prison and

04:11.260 --> 04:11.760
he died.

04:12.380 --> 04:16.640
My mother told me about Telson's Bank. My mother brought

04:16.640 --> 04:17.320
me to England.

04:18.260 --> 04:21.540
I was very young. I have lived in England all

04:21.540 --> 04:24.380
my life. But my mother taught me French.

04:25.360 --> 04:30.180
My mother died a few years ago. Lucy said. And

04:30.180 --> 04:32.400
Telson's Bank took care of me.

04:33.280 --> 04:38.680
Your father went to prison. Mr Laurie said. But he

04:38.680 --> 04:41.480
did not go to court. There was no trial.

04:42.460 --> 04:47.880
That is right, said Lucy. My father died in prison.

04:48.820 --> 04:54.980
No, my dear, said Mr Laurie. I have news of

04:54.980 --> 04:58.200
your father. He did not die in prison.

04:58.200 --> 05:04.380
He is alive and he is living in Paris. I

05:04.380 --> 05:05.580
will take you to him.

05:06.780 --> 05:12.020
Lucy Manet put her hand to her face. Miss Pross.

05:12.660 --> 05:15.960
She said loudly. Then she fainted.

05:16.980 --> 05:22.820
She fell into Mr Laurie's arms. A large woman with

05:22.820 --> 05:24.500
red hair ran into the room.

05:25.410 --> 05:29.620
I will take care of her. She shouted. I am

05:29.620 --> 05:32.080
Miss Pross. Miss Manet's companion.

05:45.140 --> 05:54.480
Chapter Two. A wine shop in Paris.

05:54.480 --> 05:57.480
A ship from Dover to Calais. Then they went by

05:57.480 --> 06:00.940
coach to Paris. They found the Defarge's

06:00.940 --> 06:06.100
wine shop in St Antoine. A wooden barrel of wine

06:06.100 --> 06:08.380
had broken in the street outside the

06:08.380 --> 06:12.320
wine shop. People were lying on the ground. They were

06:12.320 --> 06:14.940
drinking the wine. The hands and

06:14.940 --> 06:19.900
faces were red. Missier Defarge, the owner of the wine

06:19.900 --> 06:22.480
shop, was standing outside the

06:22.480 --> 06:25.060
house. He was watching the people in the street.

06:27.560 --> 06:33.060
Missier Defarge, Mr Laurie said. My name is Jarvis Laurie.

06:33.760 --> 06:36.880
This is Miss Manet. Where is

06:36.880 --> 06:40.320
Doctor Manet? We are going to take him to England.

06:41.520 --> 06:47.100
He is ill. Said Missier Defarge. My wife is taking

06:47.100 --> 06:50.580
care of him. Many years ago I was

06:50.580 --> 06:55.440
Doctor Manet's servant. He helped us then. But he went

06:55.440 --> 06:58.360
to prison. Now we are helping

06:58.360 --> 07:01.860
him. Come in. Come and see him.

07:03.260 --> 07:08.860
Mr Laurie, Lucy, Miss Pross, and Missier Defarge went into

07:08.860 --> 07:09.620
the wine shop.

07:10.920 --> 07:14.860
Madame Defarge was sitting in the shop. She was knitting

07:14.860 --> 07:17.800
with wool. Her face was hard

07:17.800 --> 07:18.820
and unkind.

07:20.040 --> 07:24.940
This is Mr Laurie. Said Missier Defarge. He wants to

07:24.940 --> 07:25.980
see Doctor Manet.

07:27.440 --> 07:33.240
Doctor Manet will not know you. Said Madame Defarge. He

07:33.240 --> 07:35.940
was in prison for 18 years. He

07:35.940 --> 07:36.900
remembers nothing.

07:38.120 --> 07:40.540
Madame Defarge looked at Lucy.

07:41.660 --> 07:43.300
Are you his daughter?

07:44.300 --> 07:45.060
She asked.

07:45.960 --> 07:51.500
Yes. Said Lucy. I am Lucy Manet. I want to

07:51.500 --> 07:52.440
see my father.

07:53.700 --> 07:57.180
Come with me. Said Madame Defarge.

07:58.320 --> 08:02.600
Madame Defarge took Mr Laurie and Lucy upstairs to a

08:02.600 --> 08:05.380
small room. An old man was

08:05.380 --> 08:09.560
sitting in the room. His hair was white. He was

08:09.560 --> 08:10.260
making shoes.

08:11.700 --> 08:14.060
Mr Laurie spoke to the old man.

08:14.860 --> 08:19.060
What is your name, Missier? He asked.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.300
The old man looked round.

08:23.600 --> 08:29.000
Prisoner number 105 North Tower. He replied.

08:31.880 --> 08:36.560
He knows his number in the Bastille prison. Said Madame

08:36.560 --> 08:37.320
Defarge.

08:38.480 --> 08:39.860
But he does not know his name.

08:41.440 --> 08:43.480
Mr Laurie was a kind man.

08:44.540 --> 08:50.140
Come with us, Doctor Manet. He said quietly. Your daughter

08:50.140 --> 08:50.780
is here.

08:51.520 --> 08:52.980
We will take you to England.

08:54.480 --> 08:59.120
Doctor Manet did not understand. Mr Laurie held the old

08:59.120 --> 08:59.820
man's arm.

09:00.580 --> 09:01.660
He led him out of the room.

09:02.940 --> 09:07.120
Doctor Manet walked slowly. He held a pair of shoes

09:07.120 --> 09:08.080
in his hand.

09:10.060 --> 09:14.660
Mr Laurie took Doctor Manet, Miss Pross and Lucy back

09:14.660 --> 09:17.100
to England. They went by ship

09:17.100 --> 09:21.900
from Calais to Dover. On the ship, Doctor Manet was

09:21.900 --> 09:25.460
weak and ill. A young man helped

09:25.460 --> 09:29.320
Lucy and Mr Laurie. They took care of Doctor Manet.

09:30.500 --> 09:34.780
You are kind, sir. Lucy said to the young man.

09:35.560 --> 09:36.880
What is your name?

09:37.900 --> 09:42.000
My name is Charles Darnay, replied the young man.

09:43.020 --> 09:44.140
Are you French?

09:45.040 --> 09:49.480
Asked Lucy. Yes, I am. Charles Darnay replied.

09:50.500 --> 09:54.160
But I live in England. I often travel between England

09:54.160 --> 09:54.740
and France.

09:56.620 --> 10:00.600
My father has been ill for a long time, said

10:00.600 --> 10:03.540
Lucy. But he will get well in England.

10:04.780 --> 10:09.540
We will meet again, said Darnay. I will visit you

10:09.540 --> 10:10.080
in England.

10:12.440 --> 10:18.160
In England, Doctor Manet slowly got well. After many months,

10:18.740 --> 10:20.240
he started to remember things.

10:20.240 --> 10:26.020
He remembered his wife. He remembered his daughter. But he

10:26.020 --> 10:28.320
did not remember the Bastille prison.

10:29.400 --> 10:31.720
And he did not remember his journey to England.

10:33.940 --> 10:37.080
Lucy and her father lived in a small house in

10:37.080 --> 10:39.500
London. Miss Pross lived with them.

10:40.400 --> 10:44.500
She took care of the house. Mr Laurie became a

10:44.500 --> 10:46.660
friend of the Manet's and Miss Pross.

10:46.660 --> 10:48.640
He often visited them.

10:49.880 --> 10:55.780
One day, Doctor Manet and Lucy received a letter. It

10:55.780 --> 10:56.960
was a letter from a lawyer.

10:58.340 --> 11:01.960
You must come to the old Bailey Law Court on

11:01.960 --> 11:04.100
Monday, the letter said.

11:04.860 --> 11:08.720
You must speak at the trial of Charles Darnay.

11:20.340 --> 11:23.180
Chapter 3. The Old Bailey

11:25.660 --> 11:29.380
Charles Darnay stood in the courtroom. He stood in front

11:29.380 --> 11:30.840
of the judge and the jury.

11:31.900 --> 11:35.940
Doctor Manet, Lucy and Mr Laurie sat at the back

11:35.940 --> 11:36.480
of the courtroom.

11:37.560 --> 11:39.300
A lawyer stood up.

11:39.300 --> 11:44.560
The lawyer spoke to the judge and the jury.

11:46.360 --> 11:50.460
Charles Darnay travelled many times between England and France.

11:51.640 --> 11:54.480
The lawyer said. There are some witnesses.

11:55.720 --> 11:59.240
These people saw Darnay in Dover and in Calais.

12:00.400 --> 12:04.420
One witness saw Darnay giving some papers to a Frenchman.

12:06.260 --> 12:07.980
Darnay is a spy.

12:10.100 --> 12:13.920
The first witness was Lucy Manet. Lucy went to the

12:13.920 --> 12:14.660
front of the courtroom.

12:15.740 --> 12:17.660
She answered the lawyer's questions.

12:18.960 --> 12:23.420
Did you see Charles Darnay on a ship? The lawyer

12:23.420 --> 12:23.820
asked.

12:24.620 --> 12:29.380
Yes, I did. Lucy replied. We were travelling from France

12:29.380 --> 12:29.940
to England.

12:30.920 --> 12:33.920
Mr Darnay often travels between England and France.

12:35.160 --> 12:38.400
Did he speak about the American colonies?

12:39.660 --> 12:43.620
The lawyer asked. No, he did not.

12:44.860 --> 12:48.740
Then the lawyer asked Doctor Manet and Mr Laurie the

12:48.740 --> 12:49.480
same questions.

12:50.540 --> 12:53.940
Doctor Manet did not remember his journey from Paris to

12:53.940 --> 12:54.200
London.

12:55.150 --> 12:58.840
Mr Laurie had not spoken to Charles Darnay.

13:00.030 --> 13:04.540
Did you see Darnay on the ship? The lawyer asked.

13:05.320 --> 13:07.520
Yes, said Mr Laurie.

13:08.740 --> 13:12.720
The next witness was a man with a crooked nose.

13:14.040 --> 13:16.680
His name was Barsad.

13:18.060 --> 13:21.460
Mr Barsad, the lawyer began.

13:22.350 --> 13:24.540
Do you often travel to France?

13:25.500 --> 13:27.480
Yes, sir. I do.

13:28.560 --> 13:29.920
answered Barsad.

13:30.680 --> 13:33.640
Did you see Charles Darnay at Calais?

13:34.860 --> 13:39.220
Yes, sir. I did. I saw him give some papers

13:39.220 --> 13:40.120
to a Frenchman.

13:41.700 --> 13:45.940
Another lawyer stood up. He was Charles Darnay's lawyer.

13:46.860 --> 13:49.060
His name was Stryver.

13:50.140 --> 13:54.620
Mr Barsad, what is your business in France?

13:55.620 --> 13:56.840
Mr Stryver asked.

13:57.780 --> 14:00.140
It is private business, sir.

14:01.080 --> 14:02.020
Barsad answered.

14:03.640 --> 14:07.200
Do you give letters or papers to Frenchmen sometimes?

14:08.260 --> 14:09.640
Asked Mr Stryver.

14:10.340 --> 14:11.620
Yes, sir.

14:12.500 --> 14:13.440
Barsad replied.

14:14.840 --> 14:18.720
Charles Darnay also has private business in France.

14:19.540 --> 14:22.980
Why are his papers different from yours?

14:24.520 --> 14:27.140
Darnay gave papers to a spy.

14:28.260 --> 14:29.860
Said Barsad, angrily.

14:31.060 --> 14:35.380
Darnay met the spy at night. I heard them speak

14:35.380 --> 14:36.960
about George Washington.

14:38.080 --> 14:41.900
Washington is a revolutionary in the American colonies.

14:44.160 --> 14:49.940
You saw Darnay and the French spy at night asked

14:49.940 --> 14:50.840
Mr Stryver.

14:51.540 --> 14:54.140
Did you see Charles Darnay clearly?

14:55.160 --> 14:58.400
Yes, sir. replied Barsad.

14:58.960 --> 15:00.640
I never forget a face.

15:02.080 --> 15:06.540
Mr Stryver's clerk was sitting next to him. Stryver pointed

15:06.540 --> 15:07.660
to this man.

15:08.260 --> 15:11.800
Mr Barsad, look at my clerk.

15:12.520 --> 15:15.800
He said, have you seen this man before?

15:17.540 --> 15:20.900
Everybody in the courtroom looked at Mr Stryver's clerk.

15:22.000 --> 15:25.720
The clerk was exactly like Charles Darnay.

15:26.940 --> 15:30.800
Mr Barsad did not answer Stryver's question.

15:32.040 --> 15:36.240
This is my clerk, Mr Sidney Carton.

15:36.840 --> 15:38.300
Said Mr Stryver.

15:38.300 --> 15:41.840
Is he like Charles Darnay?

15:42.920 --> 15:47.320
Yes, he is. Barsad replied.

15:48.500 --> 15:53.260
Did Mr Carton give some papers to a French spy

15:53.260 --> 15:54.120
in Calais?

15:55.420 --> 15:56.480
Asked Stryver.

15:57.140 --> 15:58.500
No, sir.

15:59.120 --> 16:04.640
It was dark, said Stryver. You saw a man.

16:04.640 --> 16:09.320
The man was not Mr Carton. And he was not

16:09.320 --> 16:10.760
Charles Darnay.

16:12.400 --> 16:16.920
Everybody looked at Sidney Carton again. He was exactly like

16:16.920 --> 16:17.920
Charles Darnay.

16:18.600 --> 16:19.960
Mr Stryver was right.

16:21.360 --> 16:25.120
The twelve men of the jury left the courtroom. They

16:25.120 --> 16:26.100
had to make a decision.

16:27.080 --> 16:30.720
Was Darnay guilty? Or was he not guilty?

16:30.720 --> 16:36.540
A few hours later, the jury came back into the

16:36.540 --> 16:36.820
courtroom.

16:38.060 --> 16:40.300
The judge spoke to one of the jury men.

16:41.280 --> 16:44.720
What is your decision? He asked.

16:45.920 --> 16:49.140
Not guilty. Said the jury men.

16:50.380 --> 16:53.680
Darnay is innocent. He is not a spy.

17:10.640 --> 17:11.400
Darnay is not a spy.

17:11.400 --> 17:13.360
Chapter 4. New Friends

17:15.280 --> 17:19.860
Charles Darnay was free. He stood outside the old Bailey

17:19.860 --> 17:20.540
law courts.

17:21.380 --> 17:26.020
He shook hands with everybody. Dr Manet looked at Darnay.

17:26.860 --> 17:30.240
Do I know you? Manet asked.

17:31.000 --> 17:34.740
He helped us on the ship father, said Lucy.

17:35.800 --> 17:38.200
But you do not remember our journey to England.

17:40.900 --> 17:45.560
Charles Darnay and Sidney Carton went to an inn and

17:45.560 --> 17:46.420
drank some wine.

17:47.560 --> 17:49.440
Carton drank a lot of wine.

17:50.580 --> 17:53.640
You have drunk too much, said Darnay.

17:54.140 --> 17:56.640
Do not drink any more, Mr Carton.

17:57.680 --> 18:01.420
I always drink too much, said Carton.

18:02.060 --> 18:05.840
I don't care about people. People don't care about me.

18:06.660 --> 18:09.820
But I want to drink some wine. And I want

18:09.820 --> 18:11.540
to think about Miss Lucy Manet.

18:12.480 --> 18:13.800
She's very beautiful.

18:15.740 --> 18:19.020
Charles Darnay and Sidney Carton looked at each other.

18:19.980 --> 18:24.520
They were different in some ways. Darnay was tall and

18:24.520 --> 18:24.980
handsome.

18:25.720 --> 18:29.140
He had smooth dark hair and he wore fine clothes.

18:30.120 --> 18:35.480
Carton had very pale skin and dark eyes. His hair

18:35.480 --> 18:36.820
and clothes were untidy.

18:37.860 --> 18:42.220
But the two men were like each other. Their faces

18:42.220 --> 18:43.560
were the same.

18:51.240 --> 18:55.680
Four months later, Mr Jarvis Lorry went to Dr Manet's

18:55.680 --> 18:55.940
house.

18:57.080 --> 19:00.640
The doctor and Lucy were not there. Mr Lorry talked

19:00.640 --> 19:01.760
to Miss Pross.

19:02.780 --> 19:06.640
How is Dr Manet? Asked Mr Lorry.

19:07.520 --> 19:10.740
He's well, replied Miss Pross.

19:11.260 --> 19:15.800
But sometimes he remembers the Bastille prison. Sometimes he walks

19:15.800 --> 19:17.440
round and round his room.

19:18.120 --> 19:21.540
He remembers his work in the prison. He makes shoes.

19:22.900 --> 19:26.520
Why did he go to prison? Asked Lorry.

19:27.440 --> 19:28.400
Has he told you?

19:29.280 --> 19:31.940
No, said Miss Pross.

19:31.940 --> 19:35.500
But a rich and powerful man sent him to the

19:35.500 --> 19:36.020
Bastille.

19:36.680 --> 19:40.920
In France, powerful aristocrats often send men to prison.

19:41.760 --> 19:45.660
Rich men make the laws. Innocent men go to prison

19:45.660 --> 19:46.660
without a trial.

19:47.540 --> 19:53.980
Yes, said Lorry. French aristocrats send men to prison without

19:53.980 --> 19:54.720
a trial.

19:55.520 --> 19:58.960
But now, Dr Manet's friends help him.

19:58.960 --> 20:00.700
Said Miss Pross.

20:01.160 --> 20:05.460
You are kind to him, Mr Lorry. And Mr Darnay

20:05.460 --> 20:07.980
and Mr Carton often visit our house.

20:09.140 --> 20:14.580
I like this house, said Mr Lorry. I do not

20:14.580 --> 20:16.040
have a family of my own.

20:16.500 --> 20:19.720
I visit this house and I am happy.

20:29.740 --> 20:33.000
Chapter 5, the aristocrat.

20:35.000 --> 20:37.140
It was a hot day in Paris.

20:38.460 --> 20:42.580
The Marquis Santevremond was angry. He left the palace of

20:42.580 --> 20:43.280
the king's minister.

20:44.400 --> 20:48.180
The minister had not spoken to Santevremond. The minister was

20:48.180 --> 20:50.820
too busy. He was drinking chocolate.

20:52.140 --> 20:54.000
The Marquis got into his coach.

20:55.200 --> 21:00.280
Go quickly. He shouted to the driver. Drive to the

21:00.280 --> 21:01.060
chateau.

21:02.200 --> 21:06.080
The coach went quickly through the streets of Paris. People

21:06.080 --> 21:09.160
ran away. People were afraid of the Marquis.

21:09.560 --> 21:14.320
They were afraid of the Marquis' coach and horses. Suddenly,

21:14.440 --> 21:15.640
there was a terrible cry.

21:18.280 --> 21:21.200
The driver stopped the horses at the side of the

21:21.200 --> 21:23.740
road. People came out of their houses.

21:25.220 --> 21:27.220
The Marquis shouted to the coach driver.

21:27.840 --> 21:29.060
What is wrong?

21:30.460 --> 21:32.000
Mr the Marquis.

21:32.680 --> 21:35.720
Said the driver. The child ran in front of the

21:35.720 --> 21:41.220
coach. The horses kicked the child. The child is dead.

21:42.160 --> 21:43.700
Shouted somebody in the crowd.

21:44.360 --> 21:45.320
Dead.

21:46.320 --> 21:47.520
Cried a tall man.

21:48.060 --> 21:51.260
Jack, my child is dead.

21:52.300 --> 21:55.080
Who is the father of the child?

21:55.920 --> 21:57.100
Shouted the Marquis.

21:57.580 --> 21:59.180
It is Gaspar.

21:59.860 --> 22:00.780
Said a voice.

22:01.800 --> 22:02.760
Gaspar.

22:03.380 --> 22:04.720
Shouted the Marquis.

22:05.220 --> 22:07.360
Here is some money.

22:10.360 --> 22:13.240
The Marquis threw a gold coin out of the window

22:13.240 --> 22:19.320
of the coach. Nobody moved. Nobody picked up the coin.

22:20.560 --> 22:24.240
Everybody was afraid of the Marquis. They were afraid of

22:24.240 --> 22:25.940
rich and powerful aristocrats.

22:27.820 --> 22:31.580
Then somebody threw the gold coin back into the coach.

22:32.720 --> 22:37.240
The aristocrat looked at the crowd of people. He hated

22:37.240 --> 22:40.100
them. He spoke to the coach driver.

22:40.980 --> 22:44.200
Drive to the shadow. He said.

22:45.600 --> 22:49.400
The coach moved away from the crowd. The Marquis forgot

22:49.400 --> 22:50.500
about the dead child.

22:51.840 --> 22:56.500
A man ran after the coach. But the Marquis did

22:56.500 --> 22:57.180
not see him.

23:00.360 --> 23:03.820
In the evening, the coach arrived at the shadow of

23:03.820 --> 23:04.560
Santevremond.

23:05.480 --> 23:09.180
Gabel, an old servant, was waiting for the Marquis.

23:09.940 --> 23:11.580
Mr. the Marquis.

23:12.220 --> 23:13.040
Said Gabel.

23:13.580 --> 23:18.100
I was watching your coach. A man was holding on

23:18.100 --> 23:19.240
to the back of the coach.

23:20.200 --> 23:23.220
A man? Where is he?

23:24.060 --> 23:25.320
Asked the Marquis.

23:25.320 --> 23:28.800
He jumped into the bushes beside the road.

23:30.110 --> 23:30.760
Replied Gabel.

23:31.420 --> 23:33.160
Find him quickly.

23:34.080 --> 23:35.180
Shouted the aristocrat.

23:36.020 --> 23:41.440
Now, has Missier Charles arrived? Has he come from England?

23:42.260 --> 23:44.580
No, Mr. the Marquis.

23:45.160 --> 23:46.260
Gabel replied.

23:48.380 --> 23:51.660
Later in the evening, the Marquis was in his dining

23:51.660 --> 23:54.140
room. He was eating his supper.

23:55.000 --> 23:59.360
He looked out of the window. He saw a man

23:59.360 --> 23:59.980
outside.

24:02.560 --> 24:04.820
Gabel shouted the Marquis loudly.

24:05.660 --> 24:09.040
There is a man outside the shadow. Who is he?

24:10.240 --> 24:14.100
Gabel looked out of the window. The night was dark.

24:15.060 --> 24:18.740
There is nobody outside, Mr. the Marquis.

24:19.610 --> 24:20.720
The servant said.

24:21.720 --> 24:23.280
Then Gabel listened.

24:24.480 --> 24:27.700
But I can hear something? He said.

24:28.440 --> 24:30.360
I can hear a coach.

24:31.420 --> 24:35.360
Good. My nephew Charles has arrived.

24:36.300 --> 24:37.200
Said the Marquis.

24:39.360 --> 24:43.940
A few minutes later, Charles Darnay came into the dining

24:43.940 --> 24:44.340
room.

24:47.580 --> 24:50.580
Good evening, Uncle. He said.

24:51.260 --> 24:52.730
Good evening, Charles.

24:53.900 --> 24:54.760
Said the Marquis.

24:55.240 --> 24:57.650
How is your life in England?

24:59.180 --> 25:03.260
My life is good, Uncle. Replied Charles Darnay.

25:03.920 --> 25:06.610
Why do you live in England?

25:07.940 --> 25:08.940
Said the Marquis.

25:09.440 --> 25:11.460
You must come back to France.

25:11.460 --> 25:14.420
Soon I will die.

25:15.340 --> 25:18.500
Then you will be the Marquis at Everimond.

25:19.440 --> 25:21.900
I do not want to be a Marquis.

25:22.560 --> 25:23.340
Said Darnay.

25:23.840 --> 25:26.660
I do not use the name, Santa Everimond.

25:27.180 --> 25:29.220
I do not want to be an aristocrat.

25:31.320 --> 25:32.060
Nonsense.

25:33.000 --> 25:34.400
Said the Marquis angrily.

25:35.180 --> 25:37.180
You are an aristocrat.

25:38.020 --> 25:39.580
We shall talk about this tomorrow.

25:40.820 --> 25:44.840
I do not want to talk about this, Uncle. Darnay

25:44.840 --> 25:45.100
replied.

25:46.020 --> 25:48.700
I will return to England early in the morning.

25:49.480 --> 25:50.020
Good night.

25:53.820 --> 25:55.820
The Marquis went to bed.

25:57.240 --> 25:59.680
He remembered the dead child in Paris.

26:00.640 --> 26:02.160
He remembered the tall man.

26:03.000 --> 26:04.340
The man had cried out.

26:05.360 --> 26:08.160
Dead! My child is dead!

26:09.900 --> 26:12.540
Gabelle had seen a man holding on to his coach.

26:13.640 --> 26:15.060
The Marquis remembered that.

26:15.980 --> 26:19.060
He himself had seen a man outside the window of

26:19.060 --> 26:19.720
the Chateau.

26:20.180 --> 26:21.720
He remembered that.

26:23.580 --> 26:26.100
Suddenly, the Marquis was afraid.

26:27.960 --> 26:31.080
Charles Darnay left the Chateau early in the morning.

26:31.080 --> 26:33.640
He did not speak to his uncle.

26:34.140 --> 26:35.860
He did not want to speak to his uncle.

26:36.960 --> 26:39.700
And Charles could not speak to him.

26:40.960 --> 26:43.760
The Marquis, Santa Everimond, was dead.

26:45.000 --> 26:46.100
He lay in his bed.

26:47.280 --> 26:49.280
And knife was in his chest.

27:02.460 --> 27:04.800
Chapter 6 A Wedding

27:06.860 --> 27:10.660
One day in the summer, Charles Darnay visited Dr. Manette

27:10.660 --> 27:11.900
at his house in London.

27:13.040 --> 27:17.800
Sir, he said, I am a teacher and a translator.

27:18.880 --> 27:21.780
I am a Frenchman, but I live in England.

27:22.700 --> 27:24.980
Life in France is too difficult.

27:26.000 --> 27:27.400
Yes, yes.

27:28.180 --> 27:32.900
Sir Dr. Manette, there is only bad news from France.

27:34.460 --> 27:38.120
I have often visited your house, Sir Darnay.

27:38.620 --> 27:40.960
You are a kind man and a good doctor.

27:41.940 --> 27:44.340
And I am in love with your daughter.

27:45.580 --> 27:47.900
Sir, I want to marry Lucy.

27:49.240 --> 27:51.000
Dr. Manette was surprised.

27:51.960 --> 27:54.100
Does Lucy know this?

27:54.920 --> 27:55.520
He asked.

27:55.520 --> 27:58.080
No, replied Darnay.

27:58.700 --> 27:59.980
I will ask her today.

28:00.880 --> 28:03.680
Sir, will you let me marry Lucy?

28:04.980 --> 28:07.860
Yes, said Dr. Manette.

28:08.480 --> 28:10.440
Please speak to her.

28:16.380 --> 28:20.640
A few days later, Monsieur Defarge was in his wine

28:20.640 --> 28:21.480
shop in Paris.

28:22.320 --> 28:23.560
He had some news.

28:25.160 --> 28:26.760
Gaspar is dead.

28:27.880 --> 28:29.160
Defarge said to his wife.

28:29.980 --> 28:31.160
He went to the guillotine.

28:31.940 --> 28:33.180
He died today.

28:34.980 --> 28:37.560
Gaspar killed the Marquis Antebrymond.

28:38.180 --> 28:39.700
Said Madame Defarge.

28:40.420 --> 28:42.900
But the people have suffered too much.

28:44.100 --> 28:46.480
The cruel aristocrats made the old laws.

28:47.200 --> 28:49.840
Now the people must make new laws.

28:50.840 --> 28:53.800
Soon we will kill all the aristocrats.

28:56.520 --> 28:58.120
Be careful.

28:58.880 --> 29:00.720
Said Monsieur Defarge quickly.

29:01.540 --> 29:02.900
Those are dangerous words.

29:03.700 --> 29:05.680
There is a stranger in Saint Antoine.

29:06.340 --> 29:08.060
He speaks French well.

29:08.720 --> 29:09.580
But he is English.

29:10.560 --> 29:11.400
He is a spy.

29:12.600 --> 29:14.880
His name is Basand.

29:14.880 --> 29:20.700
At that moment, Basad himself came into the shop.

29:21.660 --> 29:24.740
Good afternoon, he said.

29:25.440 --> 29:28.400
The news about Gaspar is bad.

29:29.180 --> 29:31.700
He killed the Marquis Antebrymond.

29:32.200 --> 29:34.240
Said Madame Defarge carefully.

29:34.960 --> 29:36.720
And now, he is dead.

29:37.480 --> 29:40.900
Why did Gaspar kill the Marquis?

29:41.760 --> 29:42.820
Asked Basad.

29:43.980 --> 29:45.820
Gaspar was a bad man.

29:46.640 --> 29:47.580
He was executed.

29:48.820 --> 29:50.040
Said Monsieur Defarge.

29:50.980 --> 29:54.360
Was the Marquis a bad man too?

29:55.180 --> 29:57.460
Was he executed too?

29:58.220 --> 29:59.640
Asked Basad.

30:00.280 --> 30:02.200
We know nothing about that.

30:02.940 --> 30:04.660
Monsieur Defarge said quickly.

30:05.960 --> 30:08.460
Basad bought a glass of wine.

30:09.460 --> 30:12.660
There is a new Marquis Antebrymond.

30:13.280 --> 30:14.160
He said.

30:14.960 --> 30:15.680
Yes.

30:16.480 --> 30:18.700
He is the nephew of the old Marquis.

30:19.720 --> 30:21.120
Replied Madame Defarge.

30:22.340 --> 30:24.940
The nephew, Charles.

30:25.820 --> 30:27.260
He lives in England.

30:28.600 --> 30:30.160
Basad said slowly.

30:31.240 --> 30:33.740
He looked at Madame Defarge.

30:34.680 --> 30:36.640
Does he live in England?

30:37.640 --> 30:38.920
Said Madame Defarge.

30:39.720 --> 30:41.760
She did not look at Basad.

30:42.600 --> 30:44.560
I know about you.

30:45.700 --> 30:46.640
Said Basad.

30:47.440 --> 30:50.360
Dr. Manette came out of the Bastille prison.

30:51.220 --> 30:52.580
You took care of him.

30:53.360 --> 30:54.220
Is that true?

30:55.460 --> 30:57.160
Everybody knows that.

30:57.860 --> 30:58.960
Said Madame Defarge.

30:59.840 --> 31:02.700
Many years ago, my husband was the doctor's servant.

31:03.270 --> 31:05.240
The doctor helped my family.

31:06.280 --> 31:09.600
Why did Dr. Manette go to prison?

31:10.600 --> 31:11.660
Asked Basad.

31:12.580 --> 31:15.820
Did Santebrymond send him to the Bastille?

31:16.480 --> 31:18.420
We do not know, Missier.

31:18.840 --> 31:20.340
Said Madame Defarge.

31:20.920 --> 31:23.080
You must not speak about this.

31:23.840 --> 31:25.440
Very well.

31:26.240 --> 31:27.220
Said Basad.

31:27.900 --> 31:29.980
But I can tell you some news.

31:30.840 --> 31:35.480
Dr. Manette's daughter, Lucy, is going to get married.

31:36.320 --> 31:37.860
She will be married in London.

31:38.920 --> 31:43.100
In England, her husband is called Charles Darnay.

31:43.800 --> 31:46.680
But in France, he has another name.

31:47.440 --> 31:51.660
He is Charles, Missier the Marquis and Everimand.

31:59.360 --> 32:04.260
One sunny day in London, Charles Darnay married Lucy Manette.

32:05.200 --> 32:08.620
Mr. Jarvis Laurie and Mr. Sidney Carton came to the

32:08.620 --> 32:08.880
wedding.

32:09.700 --> 32:10.880
It was a happy day.

32:12.180 --> 32:14.660
But Sidney Carton was not very happy.

32:15.920 --> 32:17.860
He shook Charles Darnay's hand.

32:17.860 --> 32:19.540
He kissed Lucy.

32:21.200 --> 32:24.900
You are my good friends, he said.

32:25.800 --> 32:27.420
I do not have many friends.

32:28.300 --> 32:29.980
Now you are married.

32:31.020 --> 32:33.420
Please let me visit your new house sometimes.

32:34.660 --> 32:38.240
You will be welcome, said Darnay.

32:38.600 --> 32:40.700
We will always be your friends.

33:04.300 --> 33:06.140
Chapter 7.

33:06.520 --> 33:07.440
Revolution.

33:09.660 --> 33:14.620
Several years past, Charles and Lucy Darnay had a daughter.

33:14.620 --> 33:18.100
They called the girl Lucy, like a mother.

33:19.100 --> 33:22.780
Sidney Carton and Jarvis Laurie often visited the family.

33:24.000 --> 33:29.420
One night, in July 1789, Mr. Laurie visited the house.

33:30.620 --> 33:34.640
I have come from Towson's bank, said Mr. Laurie.

33:35.340 --> 33:36.780
There was a lot of work today.

33:37.520 --> 33:39.040
I have news from Paris.

33:39.880 --> 33:41.140
It is not good news.

33:41.990 --> 33:46.320
The people are fighting in the streets of Paris, said

33:46.320 --> 33:46.780
Mr. Laurie.

33:47.320 --> 33:49.320
They have opened the Bastille prison.

33:50.160 --> 33:51.680
All the prisoners are free.

33:52.400 --> 33:55.960
There is a revolution in France, Mr. Laurie said.

33:56.420 --> 33:58.040
The people want a republic.

33:58.760 --> 33:59.820
They do not want a king.

34:00.680 --> 34:03.580
The people want a new government, but they do not

34:03.580 --> 34:04.640
want the aristocrats.

34:05.280 --> 34:09.280
There are many trials and many executions in Paris.

34:09.280 --> 34:10.900
The banker said.

34:11.460 --> 34:13.580
The people watch the executions.

34:14.640 --> 34:16.860
The guillotine cuts off many heads.

34:17.440 --> 34:19.840
It cuts off the heads of the aristocrats.

34:20.560 --> 34:26.100
Each time an aristocrat dies, said Mr. Laurie, the people

34:26.100 --> 34:27.040
are happy.

34:27.820 --> 34:29.940
Death to all aristocrats.

34:30.580 --> 34:33.040
They shout, long live the republic.

34:33.940 --> 34:35.600
Long live the revolution.

34:38.320 --> 34:42.700
Outside the chateau of St. everyone, the people were very

34:42.700 --> 34:43.200
angry.

34:43.880 --> 34:45.840
Kill all the aristocrats.

34:46.800 --> 34:48.000
Burn the chateau.

34:48.420 --> 34:49.060
They shouted.

34:50.860 --> 34:54.360
The servant Gabell wanted to save the chateau.

34:54.980 --> 34:56.260
But nobody helped him.

34:56.900 --> 34:58.020
The people lit fires.

34:59.140 --> 35:00.720
The chateau burned to the ground.

35:03.780 --> 35:07.020
The people wanted to kill the Marquis and everyone.

35:07.740 --> 35:09.860
But they could not find the Marquis.

35:10.500 --> 35:12.340
The old Marquis was dead.

35:13.440 --> 35:15.320
The new Marquis never came to France.

35:16.980 --> 35:19.640
The people sent Gabell to prison.

35:21.240 --> 35:22.580
Where is the Marquis?

35:23.520 --> 35:24.040
They asked him.

35:25.080 --> 35:26.880
Only the Marquis can save you.

35:34.680 --> 35:38.980
In the next months, many French aristocrats came to London.

35:40.080 --> 35:41.320
They brought news from Paris.

35:42.620 --> 35:46.140
Charles Darnay was now the Marquis and Everimonde.

35:47.180 --> 35:48.580
But he did not tell anybody.

35:49.780 --> 35:50.480
It was a secret.

35:52.340 --> 35:55.320
One day Charles received a letter from France.

35:57.000 --> 35:59.480
At the top of the letter were the words.

36:00.520 --> 36:01.700
Prison of the Abbey.

36:02.660 --> 36:03.060
Paris.

36:04.320 --> 36:08.200
To miss you Charles, the Marquis and Everimonde.

36:09.080 --> 36:09.860
The letter said.

36:10.900 --> 36:12.120
Please help me.

36:12.800 --> 36:13.700
I am in prison.

36:14.840 --> 36:16.480
I was the servant of your family.

36:17.320 --> 36:18.780
Soon I will die.

36:19.740 --> 36:21.220
Please come to Paris.

36:22.200 --> 36:23.120
Please help me.

36:24.120 --> 36:27.880
Your family servant, Tae of Field Gabell.

36:43.760 --> 36:44.760
Chapter 8.

36:45.480 --> 36:46.320
To Paris.

36:48.040 --> 36:50.680
Charles Darnay spoke to Mr. Lorry.

36:51.580 --> 36:53.960
I must go to Paris, he said.

36:54.500 --> 36:56.320
I must help a servant of my family.

36:57.480 --> 36:58.000
Paris?

36:58.800 --> 36:59.860
Said Mr. Lorry.

37:00.820 --> 37:02.680
Doctor Manette will be very worried.

37:03.420 --> 37:05.200
Your family will be very worried.

37:05.960 --> 37:07.800
Please do not tell my family today.

37:08.800 --> 37:09.440
Said Darnay.

37:10.020 --> 37:10.840
Tell them tomorrow.

37:11.700 --> 37:13.340
Tomorrow I will be in Paris.

37:14.000 --> 37:15.800
And soon I will be back in London.

37:17.080 --> 37:18.040
Very well.

37:18.900 --> 37:19.980
Said Mr. Lorry.

37:20.840 --> 37:23.240
I too must go to Paris soon.

37:24.140 --> 37:27.000
I must get some papers from Telson's Bank in Paris.

37:27.520 --> 37:28.980
I must bring them back to London.

37:30.000 --> 37:32.000
Paris is very dangerous now.

37:32.780 --> 37:34.680
The revolution has made people wild.

37:36.080 --> 37:38.680
Then I will send a message to you at Telson's

37:38.680 --> 37:38.940
Bank.

37:39.600 --> 37:40.260
Said Darnay.

37:40.740 --> 37:42.180
I will meet you in Paris.

37:44.380 --> 37:47.840
Charles Darnay went by ship from Dover to Calais.

37:49.220 --> 37:51.240
Many things in France had changed.

37:52.320 --> 37:54.900
There were many revolutionary guards in every town.

37:56.180 --> 38:00.100
French people no longer called each other Monsieur or Madame.

38:01.240 --> 38:05.140
Everybody had to be called Citizen or Citizen S.

38:05.980 --> 38:08.960
Everybody was equal in the New Republic.

38:09.940 --> 38:11.160
There were no aristocrats.

38:11.160 --> 38:13.060
There was no king.

38:18.140 --> 38:20.440
Charles went from Calais by coach.

38:21.580 --> 38:24.240
Outside the town the coach stopped.

38:25.440 --> 38:28.060
Revolutionary guards were standing in the road.

38:29.220 --> 38:30.700
Who are you Citizen?

38:32.000 --> 38:33.660
One of the Revolutionary guards asked.

38:34.740 --> 38:36.060
Show us your papers.

38:37.060 --> 38:37.780
Said another guard.

38:38.660 --> 38:40.000
Do you have a travel permit?

38:40.000 --> 38:42.120
What is your business in France?

38:43.920 --> 38:45.180
I'm going to Paris.

38:46.060 --> 38:47.000
Said Darnay.

38:47.560 --> 38:49.100
Please let me go on.

38:50.620 --> 38:52.860
This man is an aristocrat.

38:53.660 --> 38:54.860
Said the first guard.

38:55.740 --> 38:57.900
He left France and he went to England.

38:58.920 --> 39:00.520
He must go to the guillotine.

39:01.620 --> 39:04.040
I'm going to Paris on business.

39:05.000 --> 39:05.840
Darnay said.

39:06.640 --> 39:07.320
Yes.

39:08.320 --> 39:09.740
You are going to Paris.

39:10.680 --> 39:11.900
Said the second guard.

39:12.420 --> 39:13.680
You are going to prison.

39:14.480 --> 39:15.980
You are under arrest.

39:16.940 --> 39:18.800
Why am I under arrest?

39:19.340 --> 39:20.220
A Starnay angrily.

39:21.440 --> 39:23.660
You are an aristocrat.

39:24.200 --> 39:25.260
Said the first guard.

39:25.980 --> 39:29.440
All aristocrats are enemies of the revolution and enemies of

39:29.440 --> 39:29.840
the republic.

39:30.900 --> 39:33.400
All aristocrats are enemies of the people.

39:33.400 --> 39:35.360
The guillotine is waiting.

39:36.320 --> 39:37.880
It is waiting for you.

39:40.100 --> 39:43.500
A crowd of people stood around the coach.

39:44.440 --> 39:46.160
Death to all aristocrats.

39:47.080 --> 39:47.380
They shouted.

39:48.380 --> 39:49.380
Take him to Paris.

39:54.600 --> 39:57.700
The Revolutionary guards took Darnay to Paris.

39:58.940 --> 40:01.420
They put him in La Force prison.

40:04.180 --> 40:06.680
They found the letter from Gabell in his coat.

40:08.780 --> 40:11.040
This is a letter to Santa everymond.

40:11.740 --> 40:12.360
Said a guard.

40:12.980 --> 40:13.800
We know that name.

40:14.640 --> 40:16.020
The people hate that name.

40:17.720 --> 40:20.720
The next day a man visited Charles.

40:22.000 --> 40:23.600
The man was a revolutionary official.

40:24.900 --> 40:26.260
He looked at Darnay.

40:27.620 --> 40:29.240
I know your face.

40:30.140 --> 40:30.700
He said.

40:31.440 --> 40:32.900
You are Santa everymond.

40:33.740 --> 40:35.820
I am Citizen Defarge.

40:36.880 --> 40:38.340
Miss you Defarge.

40:38.940 --> 40:39.620
Said Darnay.

40:40.300 --> 40:41.500
I know your name.

40:42.260 --> 40:43.720
You helped Dr. Manette.

40:44.700 --> 40:46.680
You must call me Citizen.

40:47.560 --> 40:48.880
We are all equal now.

40:49.820 --> 40:52.160
There are no more misjures and markeyses.

40:53.240 --> 40:54.600
Citizen Defarge.

40:55.500 --> 40:57.520
Will you take a message to Telson's bank?

40:58.380 --> 40:59.060
Ask Darnay.

40:59.060 --> 41:01.820
It is a message for Mr. Laurie.

41:02.640 --> 41:04.600
He will give the message to Dr. Manette.

41:05.860 --> 41:08.180
I will not take your message.

41:09.160 --> 41:09.840
Said Defarge.

41:10.600 --> 41:11.860
You are an aristocrat.

41:12.620 --> 41:14.720
You are an enemy of the Republic.

41:16.480 --> 41:17.840
What will happen to me?

41:18.760 --> 41:19.620
Ask Darnay.

41:20.340 --> 41:23.540
There will be a trial in the people's court.

41:24.780 --> 41:27.140
Then you will go to the guillotine.

41:27.920 --> 41:29.200
Said Defarge.

41:41.880 --> 41:43.160
Chapter 9.

41:43.580 --> 41:45.280
An enemy of the Republic.

41:47.640 --> 41:50.440
Mr. Laurie was at Telson's bank in Paris.

41:51.460 --> 41:52.620
He got some news.

41:53.860 --> 41:54.860
It was bad news.

41:55.820 --> 41:58.660
Charles Darnay was in La Force Prison.

42:00.140 --> 42:02.680
Immediately Mr. Laurie sent a message to London.

42:03.720 --> 42:04.900
He sent it to Dr. Manette.

42:05.740 --> 42:09.040
Dr. Manette came to Paris with Lucy and her child.

42:10.100 --> 42:13.080
Miss Pross and Jerry Cruncher came too.

42:14.000 --> 42:15.780
They stayed in rooms near the bank.

42:17.860 --> 42:20.120
Dr. Manette spoke to Mr. Laurie.

42:21.540 --> 42:25.140
I was a prisoner in the Bastille prison for 18

42:25.140 --> 42:25.780
years.

42:26.720 --> 42:27.140
He said.

42:27.960 --> 42:29.880
The revolutionaries will listen to me.

42:30.420 --> 42:32.540
I will speak at Charles's trial.

42:33.320 --> 42:36.120
And I will speak to Miss Year and Madame Defarge.

42:36.820 --> 42:37.740
They will help us.

42:39.080 --> 42:42.440
I will speak to Madame Defarge too, said Lucy.

42:43.340 --> 42:45.920
I am a wife and I am a mother.

42:46.900 --> 42:48.180
Madame Defarge will understand.

42:48.740 --> 42:49.480
She will help us.

42:51.040 --> 42:53.780
Lucy went to the wine shop in Saint Antoine.

42:54.860 --> 42:56.600
She spoke to Madame Defarge.

42:57.560 --> 43:00.160
But Madame Defarge would not help her.

43:01.440 --> 43:05.000
Your husband is an aristocrat, she said.

43:05.600 --> 43:06.780
Now he is in prison.

43:07.980 --> 43:11.880
Before the revolution, the aristocrat sent poor people to prison.

43:12.540 --> 43:13.240
We were helpless.

43:14.860 --> 43:18.320
Now all that is finished, Madame Defarge said.

43:18.320 --> 43:21.000
The aristocrats have finished too.

43:21.960 --> 43:24.200
Your husband's trial will be tomorrow.

43:25.100 --> 43:26.140
I cannot help you.

43:29.440 --> 43:30.980
Charles, Saint Evermond.

43:31.820 --> 43:33.700
Also called Charles Darnay.

43:35.460 --> 43:38.000
The President of the Court shouted the name.

43:38.900 --> 43:40.200
Charles Darnay stood up.

43:41.160 --> 43:42.400
He stood in front of the judges.

43:43.640 --> 43:44.820
He answered their questions.

43:46.040 --> 43:49.460
You are an aristocrat and an enemy of the Republic.

43:50.300 --> 43:51.320
Said the President.

43:52.160 --> 43:54.560
No, answered Darnay.

43:55.140 --> 43:57.160
I do not live in France.

43:57.940 --> 44:00.180
I have not treated the French people badly.

44:00.980 --> 44:03.320
I did not take money from the people.

44:03.940 --> 44:06.600
I do not want to be the Marquis Saint Evermond.

44:07.800 --> 44:09.080
Are there witnesses?

44:09.980 --> 44:11.060
asked the President.

44:11.760 --> 44:13.740
Will somebody speak for you?

44:15.120 --> 44:15.700
Yes.

44:16.700 --> 44:21.500
Citizen Teofield Gabelle and Dr. Alexandra Manette will speak for

44:21.500 --> 44:21.700
me.

44:22.340 --> 44:22.920
Said Darnay.

44:24.700 --> 44:25.900
Gabelle spoke first.

44:27.500 --> 44:31.080
Charles Darnay did not want to be the Marquis Saint

44:31.080 --> 44:31.660
Evermond.

44:32.180 --> 44:33.000
He said.

44:33.720 --> 44:35.660
He did not want to be an aristocrat.

44:36.460 --> 44:38.820
He did not take any money from the people of

44:38.820 --> 44:39.120
France.

44:40.080 --> 44:41.280
He is a good man.

44:43.060 --> 44:45.300
Then Dr. Manette spoke.

44:46.440 --> 44:49.840
I was a prisoner in the Bastille for 18 years.

44:50.780 --> 44:51.160
He said.

44:52.160 --> 44:53.860
The people in the courtroom cheered.

44:54.820 --> 44:56.540
Long live Dr. Manette.

44:57.420 --> 44:57.820
They shouted.

44:59.380 --> 45:01.280
Charles Darnay helped me.

45:02.040 --> 45:02.900
The doctor said.

45:03.680 --> 45:06.480
I was very sick and he took care of me.

45:07.140 --> 45:08.480
He married my daughter.

45:09.360 --> 45:10.460
He is a good man.

45:11.260 --> 45:12.620
He came back to France.

45:13.540 --> 45:15.800
He wants to help Citizen Gabelle.

45:17.660 --> 45:20.220
The people in the courtroom cheered again.

45:21.080 --> 45:22.340
Long live the Republic.

45:23.460 --> 45:25.280
Long live the people of France.

45:26.080 --> 45:26.540
They shouted.

45:28.140 --> 45:30.300
Charles Darnay was arrested in England.

45:31.220 --> 45:32.240
Dr. Manette said.

45:33.020 --> 45:34.080
The English said.

45:34.580 --> 45:36.380
Darnay is a French spy.

45:37.180 --> 45:39.920
He is a friend of the revolutionaries in the American

45:39.920 --> 45:40.420
colonies.

45:41.320 --> 45:44.540
Now you say he is an enemy of France.

45:45.380 --> 45:46.260
You are wrong.

45:47.400 --> 45:49.040
Let him go.

45:49.920 --> 45:51.440
Shouted the people in the courtroom.

45:52.320 --> 45:54.000
He is a friend of the revolution.

45:55.180 --> 45:57.340
The judges made their decision.

45:58.540 --> 45:59.720
Not guilty.

46:00.580 --> 46:02.000
The president said.

46:03.020 --> 46:04.360
He spoke to Darnay.

46:05.360 --> 46:06.660
You are free.

46:08.120 --> 46:08.560
He said.

46:25.140 --> 46:26.400
Chapter 10.

46:27.360 --> 46:28.540
Citizen Barsad.

46:29.880 --> 46:32.920
Charles Darnay stood outside the courtroom.

46:32.920 --> 46:34.740
He was free.

46:35.680 --> 46:37.340
He held Lucy in his arms.

46:38.660 --> 46:39.880
He is innocent.

46:40.440 --> 46:41.700
I have saved him.

46:42.420 --> 46:43.320
Said Dr. Manette.

46:43.960 --> 46:45.220
Let's go home now.

46:46.900 --> 46:49.260
They returned to their rooms near the bank.

46:50.220 --> 46:52.840
Jerry Cruncher and Miss Pross went out to buy some

46:52.840 --> 46:53.180
wine.

46:54.120 --> 46:57.540
A little later the doctor was talking to Charles and

46:57.540 --> 46:57.760
Lucy.

46:58.920 --> 47:02.240
Suddenly some revolutionary guards came into the room.

47:02.920 --> 47:05.020
One of the guards spoke to Charles.

47:06.680 --> 47:08.040
Citizen Everymond.

47:08.620 --> 47:09.920
Also called Darnay.

47:10.420 --> 47:11.420
You were under arrest.

47:12.220 --> 47:12.780
He said.

47:13.780 --> 47:15.820
Why is he under arrest?

47:16.480 --> 47:17.460
Asked Dr. Manette.

47:18.060 --> 47:18.900
There was a trial.

47:19.860 --> 47:20.700
He is not guilty.

47:21.600 --> 47:22.940
He is free now.

47:23.700 --> 47:25.860
There will be another trial tomorrow.

47:26.920 --> 47:27.520
Said the guard.

47:28.500 --> 47:30.240
What has he done wrong?

47:30.900 --> 47:32.520
Said Dr. Manette angrily.

47:32.920 --> 47:34.340
Who accuses him?

47:35.180 --> 47:36.580
You will know tomorrow.

47:37.740 --> 47:38.500
Said the guard.

47:39.560 --> 47:42.940
The guards took Darnay back to La Force prison.

47:44.260 --> 47:44.940
Lucy cried.

47:46.280 --> 47:48.120
Her father held her in his arms.

47:49.460 --> 47:51.420
I have saved him once.

47:52.500 --> 47:53.440
Said Dr. Manette.

47:54.460 --> 47:55.940
I will save him again.

47:56.780 --> 47:59.120
I will speak at the trial tomorrow.

48:02.040 --> 48:06.320
Jerry Cruncher and Miss Pross were looking for some wine.

48:07.520 --> 48:10.560
They went into Miss Yuramadam Defarge's wine shop.

48:11.640 --> 48:15.360
Miss Pross saw a man inside the shop.

48:16.480 --> 48:17.460
She cried out.

48:18.460 --> 48:19.100
Solomon.

48:20.400 --> 48:21.780
What do you want?

48:22.520 --> 48:23.860
Said the man in English.

48:24.860 --> 48:25.540
He was angry.

48:26.920 --> 48:27.330
Solomon.

48:29.120 --> 48:30.020
Said Miss Pross.

48:30.360 --> 48:32.700
You are my brother, Solomon.

48:33.520 --> 48:36.180
I have not seen you for many years.

48:37.160 --> 48:38.500
Be quiet.

48:39.680 --> 48:40.560
Said the man.

48:41.220 --> 48:43.140
I have a different name now.

48:43.960 --> 48:45.760
I am a revolutionary official.

48:46.800 --> 48:49.020
I am an important man in the Republic.

48:50.800 --> 48:53.440
His name is Citizen Barsad.

48:54.160 --> 48:55.440
Said another man.

48:55.440 --> 48:58.820
They all turned and looked at the person who had

48:58.820 --> 48:59.160
spoken.

49:00.780 --> 49:01.420
Darnay.

49:01.980 --> 49:03.120
Said Barsad.

49:03.480 --> 49:04.980
Why are you here?

49:05.940 --> 49:08.720
No. I am not Charles Darnay.

49:09.240 --> 49:09.900
Said the man.

49:10.640 --> 49:12.660
My name is Sydney Carton.

49:13.340 --> 49:15.200
You saw me at the trial in London.

49:16.300 --> 49:18.440
My face is like Darnay's face.

49:19.580 --> 49:20.820
But I am not Darnay.

49:20.820 --> 49:24.820
I want to see Darnay and his wife Lucy Carton.

49:26.060 --> 49:27.140
Where are they?

49:28.220 --> 49:30.020
Darnay is under arrest.

49:30.980 --> 49:31.820
Said Barsad.

49:32.520 --> 49:34.440
He is in La Force Prison.

49:35.400 --> 49:36.780
He will go to the guillotine.

